result.execSummary:
The defendant Alexander R. Nickel was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • Criminal Damage to Property, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

[ma] Case called at 9:35am 
Defendant Alexander R. Nickel in court.  Attorney Kayla Barteck in court for Alexander R. Nickel.  Attorney Theresa Beck in court for State of Wisconsin. 

Constitutional rights are reviewed; pleas of " NO CONTEST " entered on Counts #1 and #3; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance is verified.  The Court accepts the plea, finds the Defendant guilty, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

On Motion of the State, the Court reads-in and dismisses Counts #2 and #4

Sentencing recommendations/ arguments given by Counsel 
Statement made by Victim

On Count # 1 the Court sentences Mr. Nickel to 80 days jail, concurrent to Count #3.
On Count #3 the Court sentences Mr. Nickel to 4 months jail, concurrent to Count #1.  

The Court STAYS these sentences and places the Defendant on Probation for 2 years, with conditions:
--to undergo AODA assessment and follow through with recommended treatment per Agent
--to undergo any other assessment, treatment, or counseling per Agent
--complete anger management counseling program 
--to comply with DNA sample provision 
--no contact with Victim 1 or Victim 2
--no violent contact with GAA
--payment of costs, fees and surcharges 
--payment of restitution in the amount of $500 to Victim 2

Days credit for time already served:  1  day

The Court finds Mr. Nickel NOT eligible for expungement.
